---
title: "Is QED Necessary?"
year: 1966
abstract: >
  Jaynes examines the assumption that Quantum Electrodynamics (QED) holds
  absolute validity in optical coherence and quantum electronics. Adopting the
  posture of the Devil's Advocate, he proposes that semiclassical theories
  should be judged by experiment rather than agreement with QED. He surveys the
  theoretical and experimental landscape, suggesting new optical tests using
  modern technology to resolve issues concerning spontaneous emission, the
  photoelectric effect, and uncertainty relations.
author: ["E.T. Jaynes"]
categories: ["Quantum Mechanics & Advanced Physics"]
